The paper deals with video-to-video translation tasks such as super-resolution, inpainting, and style transfer, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves transferring a well-trained image model to a video model, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the challenges of achieving temporal consistency in video models, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves aggregating over temporally localized windows, which is a graph-based approach (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves developing a method for video-to-video translation tasks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
